</taxonomicName>
by campanulate (not narrowly tubular) floral tube, zygomorphic (not actinomorphic) corolla, exserted (not included) stamens (
<figureCitation id="A49E2A68E6323C26FCFB073DFCAFFE86" box="[783,840,356,378]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,229,1946,1968]" captionTargetBox="[344,1249,466,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-151@1.[335,1252,458,1918]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Oreocharis hainanensis S.J.Ling &amp; M.X. Ren sp. nov. A. Habitat; B. habit; C. adaxial leaf surface; D. abaxial leaf surface; E. lateral view of corolla, sepal and calyx; F. face view of corolla; G. opening flower showing stamens and staminode; H. pistil, stamens and staminode; I. capsule; J. fruit pods; K. seeds; L–N. Main floral visitors: L. Braunapis sp.; M. Apis sp.; N. Amegilla sp.; All photos by Shao-Jun Ling." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6340387" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6340387/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="288">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
